  "text": "Bisulfite treatment of gDNA was done as described previously. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] gDNA, 2 g in a volume of 100 L, was denatured in 0.2 N NaOH at 37°C for 10 minutes and incubated with 3 M sodium bisulfite at 50°C for 16 hours. After incubation, modified DNA was purified using Wizard DNA Clean-Up System (Promega) according to the manufacturer's instructions and was desulfonated in 0.3 N NaOH at room temperature for 5 minutes. DNA was then ethanol precipitated, washed, and resuspended in 20 L water and used immediately or stored at Ϫ20°C until use.",
